The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage
                                                                                                                                                             1                                              Creator of history, cheated in historys blunder            Jyoti Basu, who ruled Bengal for a record 23 years but was stopped by his party from becoming Prime Minister, died today minutes before noon after a 17-day battle with pneumonia.  ... |                                                 Mamata Banerjee today paid tributes to Jyoti Basu but packed in a punch at his party, saying he was the last chapter of the Left movement in Bengal. ... |                                         The day Jyoti Basu died, Somnath Chatterjee, the former Lok Sabha Speaker, rekindled the debate on his expulsion from the CPM. ... |                                         Unlike Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee, Jyoti Basu was never known as a politician who would court controversy. ... |                                         His advice was statesman-like but always pragmatic and based on unshakable values ... |                                         Jyoti Basu lost his last medical battle because his lungs, virtually the only organs that had never given him trouble, failed him. ... |                                                                                                                                                                                   Jyoti Basu is no more with us. He has left us. I cant speak any more
  BIMAN BOSE
